rs debt securities in structured finance possess priority as creditors to specific pools of assets this status means that they receive payment before shareholders and other creditors depending on the type of debt securities an investor holds and the security pledged to support it some debt holders rank higher in repayment precedence than othersstructured finance techniques generally enable firms to obtain access to more capital at lower interest because they are backed by actual assets or collateral that produce cash flows or that which can be traded or sold to repay debt holders these assets represent the opportunity to collect funds from issuers or courts under well established legal constructs when a corporation issues debt securities using structured finance techniques the assets and the legal documentation governing the rights to collateral are of primary importance using structured finance a company’s credit rating is not as relevant to the determination of the interest rates as is the collateral as a source of repayment in satisfaction of the debt filed under debt bonds jon sabes  notes november   sec registration basics jon sabes holds the position of chief executive officer of minneapolisbased gwg holdings inc and of medfinance both of which he established nearly  years ago one of the companies gwg holdings inc has filed a registration statement under the securities act of  also known as the truth in securities law the securities act of  strived to provide protection to investors by creating transparency about the financial health of organizations issuing securities overseen by the united states securities and exchange commission the securities act of  requires organizations to disclose crucial financial information upon mandatory registration of securities registration with the united states securities and exchange commission entails reporting descriptions about gwg holdings inc’s business and property meticulous details about the securities themselves ind